        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>1000 and 3000 and 4000 Models built prior to November 1, 1997 may experience a false signal to the
                    hydraulic warning light and buzzer due to poor grounding or defective brake light bulb at the rear
                    of the vehicle. To correct this issue, the installation of a relay (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0008061">Figure 1</hotlnk>
                    and
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0008062">Figure 2</hotlnk>) is recommended. In addition, troubleshooting
                    information and a Diagnostic Flow Chart (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0008063">Figure 3</hotlnk>) are included to guide you through the troubleshooting
                    process.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
